limerick_list.text:
B. bubalis bubalis might mean
Wa-wa-wow! Water buffalo scene.
Didelphis plays dead;
Mama Mae married Ned;
And cacao is the chocolate bean.

In the chorus, cast off to one side;
In the back, just along for the ride;
And left standing in hallways,
Alas, I am always
A bridesmaid, but never the bride.

I know that you're stricken with gout;
My advice is to be more devout.
There's no miracle pill
For this kind of an ill;
Its curableness is in doubt.

A cruive is this hovel (don't sneer);
Or this pigsty, or pen (for a steer);
This low fence (none disturbs
My few veggies and herbs);
Or this salmon-coop placed in a weir.
